OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused's ex-
OL,4,Cgirlfriend tells court he hit her
OL,6,FThe woman said Mr McCullagh went into
OL,7,Fthe garden for a cigarette and there
OL,8,Fwas "a bit of a tussle" when she tried
OL,9,Fto "gently" pull him back into the
OL,10,Fhouse and he pushed her "abruptly" .
OL,12,FMr Kearney suggested this was because
OL,13,Fthe defendant did not want physical
OL,14,Fcontact, while the woman was a "touchy
OL,15,Ffeely" person.
OL,26,@pD@EOUpD@WO]qD@DOUqD@KO]rD@YOUrD@bO]vD@
OL,26,A`OUwD@FO]
