OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1772975481
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused's ex-
OL,4,Cgirlfriend tells court he hit her
OL,6,FThey continued to argue past midnight
OL,7,Fand left the house in the early hours
OL,8,Fof the morning, with Mr McCullagh
OL,9,Fdriving and the woman wearing a
OL,10,Fdressing gown and pyjamas, the court
OL,11,Fheard.
OL,13,FFirst, she said, he tried to bring her
OL,14,Fto the house of the man she had been
OL,15,Fmessaging saying: "If you are talking
OL,16,Fto him, if you want him as much as you
OL,17,Fsaid, I will bring you there right
OL,18,Fnow."
OL,26,@wD@SOUzD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/21
