OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1772975481
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused's ex-
OL,4,Cgirlfriend tells court he hit her
OL,6,FHe also said he would "burn" and
OL,7,F"destroy" sentimental possessions of
OL,8,Fhers.
OL,10,FMr Kearney said Mr McCullagh claimed
OL,11,Fto have said: "A lesser man would
OL,12,Fsmash your Playstation, or burn your
OL,13,Fstuff".
OL,15,FAfter "pleading" with him, she said he
OL,16,F"finally said he would bring them back
OL,17,Fto me".
