PN,44317
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1772975481
OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused's ex-
OL,4,Cgirlfriend tells court he hit her
OL,6,FShe then went to hospital where her
OL,7,Fbaby was still born.
OL,9,FMr McCullagh supported her in
OL,10,Fhospital, with Mr Kearney describing
OL,11,Fhim as having "manned up" and
OL,12,Fafterwards he brought her back to his
OL,13,Fhome where she lived for several
OL,14,Fmonths.
OL,16,FSuffering from poor mental health, she
OL,17,Fsought help from counselling services
OL,18,Fin the following months and
OL,19,Fcounsellors came to Mr McCullagh's
OL,20,Fhouse where she was living for the
OL,21,Fsessions.
OL,26,@sD@OOUsD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G17/21
