OL,3,CNatalie McNally murder accused's ex-
OL,4,Cgirlfriend tells court he hit her
OL,6,FIn cross examination the woman
OL,7,Frevealed she had mental health issues
OL,8,Fand that she had struggled "with
OL,9,Fvoices and self harm" which created
OL,10,F"tensions" between the couple.
OL,12,FResponding to Mr Kearney she agreed
OL,13,Fthe defendant had "tried to help" her.
OL,15,FShe also agreed that Mr McCullagh
OL,16,F"wouldn't be the sort of man to talk",
OL,17,Fsometimes she would "talk to him when
OL,18,Fhe didn't want to talk" and that he
OL,19,Fwould have tried to talk to her "in
OL,20,Fhis own way".
